From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0040/N] UnixConstants.java.template: prefer __linux__ over _ALLBSD_SOURCE for ENOATTR

The template gates `XATTR_NOT_FOUND` selection on
`_ALLBSD_SOURCE` first, falling through to `__linux__`:

  #ifdef _ALLBSD_SOURCE
      static final int PREFIX_XATTR_NOT_FOUND = ENOATTR;
  #elif __linux__
      static final int PREFIX_XATTR_NOT_FOUND = ENODATA;
  #else
      static final int PREFIX_XATTR_NOT_FOUND = 00;
  #endif

For our cross-build, the BUILDJDK gensrc pass runs the HOST CPP
(x86 Linux glibc) with `-D_ALLBSD_SOURCE` (set by our patch 0037).
Both `_ALLBSD_SOURCE` and `__linux__` are defined; the BSD branch
wins, but glibc doesn't define `ENOATTR` — the generated Java
becomes `static final int XATTR_NOT_FOUND = ENOATTR;` (cannot
find symbol).

Swap to check `__linux__` first (with `_ALLBSD_SOURCE`
exclusion). This makes the BUILDJDK pass on Linux pick ENODATA
(the right Linux value), while a true BSD/CheriBSD target build
still hits the BSD branch.

Refs: docs/05_zgc_cheri_collision_report.md §6 (patch 0040)

--- a/src/java.base/unix/classes/sun/nio/fs/UnixConstants.java.template
+++ b/src/java.base/unix/classes/sun/nio/fs/UnixConstants.java.template
@@ -118,9 +118,9 @@
 #endif

 // fgetxattr error codes for absent attributes depend on the OS:
-#ifdef _ALLBSD_SOURCE
+#if defined(_ALLBSD_SOURCE) && !defined(__linux__)
     static final int PREFIX_XATTR_NOT_FOUND = ENOATTR;
-#elif __linux__
+#elif defined(__linux__)
     static final int PREFIX_XATTR_NOT_FOUND = ENODATA;
 #else
     // not supported (dummy values will not be used at runtime).
